   GLOBE Stars:
   Find the Hidden GLOBE Students
   Where in the world are those other GLOBE students? That's the question
   three groups of students had about each other. They had to locate other
   GLOBE schools armed with just a handful of clues, including GLOBE data.
   More...


   New Optional Soil and Air Temp Data Logger Protocol

   Have you ever wondered how hibernating animals survive the winter in
   their burrows or why a cement walkway feels so cold in the morning?
   Studies of diurnal soil and air temperature records can help you answer
   both questions. Daily soil temperature data collected using the current
   GLOBE Soil Temperature protocol are important for research but
   measurements taken many times each day and at 50 cm depth in addition
   to 5 cm and 10 cm open many additional areas of investigation. More
   [sanantonio_sm.gif] GLOBE Teachers Conference

   There will be a GLOBE Teachers Conference in San Antonio, Texas, July
   15-17, 2002. The conference, open to as many GLOBE teachers as space
   permits, will help teachers guide student investigations using GLOBE
   Data. Such investigations can be submitted in a later competition for
   invitations to special 2003 events. More
